[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":948},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Freact\u002F2022\u002F10\u002F10\u002Flearn-react-now-26-react-router-link-navlink\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Freact\u002F2022\u002F10\u002F10\u002Flearn-react-now-26-react-router-link-navlink\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Freact\u002F2022\u002F10\u002F10\u002Flearn-react-now-26-react-router-link-navlink\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Freact\u002F2022\u002F10\u002F10\u002Flearn-react-now-26-react-router-link-navlink\u002F":925,"related:\u002Fen\u002Freact\u002F2022\u002F10\u002F10\u002Flearn-react-now-26-react-router-link-navlink\u002F":934},"\u002Freact\u002F20221010\u002F1703126745\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":905,"date":906,"description":907,"extension":908,"lang":909,"meta":910,"navigation":400,"path":911,"readingMinutes":912,"seo":913,"standalone":914,"stem":915,"tags":916,"tldr":922,"updated":906,"url":923,"__hash__":924},"content\u002Fen\u002FReact\u002Flearn-react-now-26-react-router-link-navlink.md","You'll Learn React Eventually, So Why Not Now? - React Router - Link and NavLink - (26)","1003025061",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":899},"minimark",[11,16,32,35,48,54,70,76,128,135,159,173,184,199,261,270,300,303,313,316,333,342,351,597,610,617,623,629,632,642,677,687,718,728,731,785,794,830,836,842,858,871,879,883,886,895],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19,20,24,25,27,28,31],"p",{},"We touched on ",[21,22,23],"code",{},"Link"," earlier, but we never really got to know it properly — we just showed how to use it and moved on. So in this post I want to take a closer look at ",[21,26,23],{},", and along the way introduce another piece too: ",[21,29,30],{},"NavLink",".",[12,33,23],{"id":34},"link",[17,36,37,38,40,41,44,45,47],{},"Even though we used ",[21,39,23],{}," in the previous chapter, we only ever touched its ",[21,42,43],{},"to"," prop. But ",[21,46,23],{}," actually has quite a few props you can use, so let's take a look at what's available.",[17,49,50,51,53],{},"First, the most basic way to write ",[21,52,23],{}," looks like this:",[55,56,61],"pre",{"className":57,"code":58,"language":59,"meta":60,"style":60},"language-jsx shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","\u003CLink to=\"\u002F\">Home\u003C\u002FLink>\n","jsx","",[21,62,63],{"__ignoreMap":60},[64,65,68],"span",{"class":66,"line":67},"line",1,[64,69,58],{},[17,71,72,73,75],{},"The ",[21,74,43],{}," prop can actually accept two kinds of things. The most basic one is a String, which is what you saw above. The other is an Object, and that Object can take a few props:",[55,77,79],{"className":57,"code":78,"language":59,"meta":60,"style":60},"\u003CLink to={{\n  pathname: '\u002F',\n  search: '?q=ray',\n  hash: '#app',\n  state: {\n    abc: true,\n  }\n}}>Home\u003C\u002FLink>\n",[21,80,81,86,92,98,104,110,116,122],{"__ignoreMap":60},[64,82,83],{"class":66,"line":67},[64,84,85],{},"\u003CLink to={{\n",[64,87,89],{"class":66,"line":88},2,[64,90,91],{},"  pathname: '\u002F',\n",[64,93,95],{"class":66,"line":94},3,[64,96,97],{},"  search: '?q=ray',\n",[64,99,101],{"class":66,"line":100},4,[64,102,103],{},"  hash: '#app',\n",[64,105,107],{"class":66,"line":106},5,[64,108,109],{},"  state: {\n",[64,111,113],{"class":66,"line":112},6,[64,114,115],{},"    abc: true,\n",[64,117,119],{"class":66,"line":118},7,[64,120,121],{},"  }\n",[64,123,125],{"class":66,"line":124},8,[64,126,127],{},"}}>Home\u003C\u002FLink>\n",[17,129,130,131,134],{},"This Object basically mirrors the ",[21,132,133],{},"window.location"," properties, mainly these:",[136,137,138,144,149,154],"ul",{},[139,140,141],"li",{},[21,142,143],{},"pathname",[139,145,146],{},[21,147,148],{},"search",[139,150,151],{},[21,152,153],{},"hash",[139,155,156],{},[21,157,158],{},"state",[17,160,161,163,164,166,167,169,170,172],{},[21,162,143],{}," is pretty straightforward — it does the same thing as writing a plain ",[21,165,43],{}," string path. And when you set ",[21,168,148],{}," and ",[21,171,153],{},", clicking the link gives you a URL like this:",[55,174,178],{"className":175,"code":176,"language":177,"meta":60,"style":60},"language-txt shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","http:\u002F\u002Fexample\u002F#\u002F?q=ray#app\n","txt",[21,179,180],{"__ignoreMap":60},[64,181,182],{"class":66,"line":67},[64,183,176],{},[17,185,186,187,189,190,192,193,195,196,198],{},"The interesting one in here is ",[21,188,158],{},". ",[21,191,158],{}," is a way to pass data along, but there's an important thing to watch out for: from React Router v6 onwards, ",[21,194,158],{}," is no longer written inside ",[21,197,43],{}," — it goes outside of it:",[55,200,202],{"className":57,"code":201,"language":59,"meta":60,"style":60},"\u003CLink to={{\n  pathname: '\u002Fproducts',\n  }}\n  state={{\n    products: {\n      id: '1',\n      name: 'QQ Product'\n    }\n  }}>\n  Product Detail\n\u003C\u002FLink>\n",[21,203,204,208,213,218,223,228,233,238,243,249,255],{"__ignoreMap":60},[64,205,206],{"class":66,"line":67},[64,207,85],{},[64,209,210],{"class":66,"line":88},[64,211,212],{},"  pathname: '\u002Fproducts',\n",[64,214,215],{"class":66,"line":94},[64,216,217],{},"  }}\n",[64,219,220],{"class":66,"line":100},[64,221,222],{},"  state={{\n",[64,224,225],{"class":66,"line":106},[64,226,227],{},"    products: {\n",[64,229,230],{"class":66,"line":112},[64,231,232],{},"      id: '1',\n",[64,234,235],{"class":66,"line":118},[64,236,237],{},"      name: 'QQ Product'\n",[64,239,240],{"class":66,"line":124},[64,241,242],{},"    }\n",[64,244,246],{"class":66,"line":245},9,[64,247,248],{},"  }}>\n",[64,250,252],{"class":66,"line":251},10,[64,253,254],{},"  Product Detail\n",[64,256,258],{"class":66,"line":257},11,[64,259,260],{},"\u003C\u002FLink>\n",[17,262,263,264,266,267,269],{},"By passing data through the ",[21,265,158],{}," prop, you can carry the previous page's data over to the next page when you navigate. Then you grab that ",[21,268,158],{}," data like this:",[55,271,273],{"className":57,"code":272,"language":59,"meta":60,"style":60},"const { state } = useLocation();\n  \nuseEffect(() => {\n  console.log(state); \u002F\u002F { products: { id: '1', name: 'QQ Product' } }\n},[]);\n",[21,274,275,280,285,290,295],{"__ignoreMap":60},[64,276,277],{"class":66,"line":67},[64,278,279],{},"const { state } = useLocation();\n",[64,281,282],{"class":66,"line":88},[64,283,284],{},"  \n",[64,286,287],{"class":66,"line":94},[64,288,289],{},"useEffect(() => {\n",[64,291,292],{"class":66,"line":100},[64,293,294],{},"  console.log(state); \u002F\u002F { products: { id: '1', name: 'QQ Product' } }\n",[64,296,297],{"class":66,"line":106},[64,298,299],{},"},[]);\n",[17,301,302],{},"Pretty simple, right?",[17,304,305,306,31],{},"To keep things from getting too confusing, I've put a stripped-down version of the example code ",[307,308,312],"a",{"href":309,"rel":310},"https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fexample-react-router-link",[311],"nofollow","over here",[12,314,30],{"id":315},"navlink",[17,317,318,319,322,323,325,326,329,330,332],{},"Next up is another way to navigate between pages: ",[21,320,321],{},"\u003CNavLink \u002F>",". In short, ",[21,324,321],{}," is basically a souped-up version of ",[21,327,328],{},"\u003CLink \u002F>",". Why do I say that? Because it can track the page you're currently on and give it a matching state, which makes it really handy for building navbar links. First, here's the basic ",[21,331,321],{}," syntax:",[55,334,336],{"className":57,"code":335,"language":59,"meta":60,"style":60},"\u003CNavLink to=\"\u002F\">Home\u003C\u002FNavLink>\n",[21,337,338],{"__ignoreMap":60},[64,339,340],{"class":66,"line":67},[64,341,335],{},[17,343,344,345,347,348,350],{},"So what do I mean by \"tracking the page and giving it a matching state\"? Let me borrow the navbar from the ToDoList we built and swap all the ",[21,346,23],{},"s for ",[21,349,30],{},"s. I'm reusing the ToDoList navbar purely because it's convenient to demo with. So right now main.jsx looks like this:",[55,352,354],{"className":57,"code":353,"language":59,"meta":60,"style":60},"import React from 'react'\nimport { HashRouter, NavLink, Routes, Route } from \"react-router-dom\";\nimport ReactDOM from 'react-dom\u002Fclient'\nimport App from '.\u002FApp'\nimport ToDoList from '.\u002FToDoList'\nimport Products from '.\u002FProducts'\nimport Admin from '.\u002FAdmin'\nimport '.\u002Findex.css';\n\nReactDOM.createRoot(document.getElementById('root')).render(\n  \u003CReact.StrictMode>\n    \u003CHashRouter>\n      \u003Cnav className=\"px-5 flex items-center h-[60px] bg-indigo-500 text-white\">\n        \u003Ch1 className=\"mr-auto text-2xl\">React TodoList\u003C\u002Fh1>\n        \u003Cul className=\"flex\">\n          \u003Cli className=\"mr-3\">\n            \u003CNavLink to=\"\u002Fhome\" className=\"border p-3 hover:bg-indigo-600 duration-500\"\n            >Home\u003C\u002FNavLink>\n          \u003C\u002Fli>\n          \u003Cli className=\"mr-3\">\n            \u003CNavLink to=\"\u002Ftodolist\" className=\"border p-3 hover:bg-indigo-600 duration-500\">ToDoList\u003C\u002FNavLink>\n          \u003C\u002Fli>\n          \u003Cli className=\"mr-3\">\n          \u003CNavLink to='\u002Fproducts'\n            className=\"border p-3 hover:bg-indigo-600 duration-500\"\n            >Product Detail\u003C\u002FNavLink>\n          \u003C\u002Fli>\n          \u003Cli className=\"mr-3\">\n          \u003CNavLink to='\u002Fadmin'\n            className=\"border p-3 hover:bg-indigo-600 duration-500\"\n            >Admin\u003C\u002FNavLink>\n          \u003C\u002Fli>\n        \u003C\u002Ful>\n      \u003C\u002Fnav>\n      \u003CRoutes>\n        \u003CRoute path=\"\u002F\" element={ \u003CApp \u002F> } \u002F>\n        \u003CRoute path=\"\u002Ftodolist\" element={ \u003CToDoList \u002F> } \u002F>\n        \u003CRoute path=\"\u002Fproducts\" element={ \u003CProducts \u002F> } \u002F>\n        \u003CRoute path=\"\u002Fadmin\" element={ \u003CAdmin \u002F> } \u002F>\n      \u003C\u002FRoutes>\n    \u003C\u002FHashRouter>\n  \u003C\u002FReact.StrictMode>\n)\n",[21,355,356,361,366,371,376,381,386,391,396,402,407,412,418,424,430,436,442,448,454,460,465,471,476,481,487,493,499,504,509,515,520,526,531,537,543,549,555,561,567,573,579,585,591],{"__ignoreMap":60},[64,357,358],{"class":66,"line":67},[64,359,360],{},"import React from 'react'\n",[64,362,363],{"class":66,"line":88},[64,364,365],{},"import { HashRouter, NavLink, Routes, Route } from \"react-router-dom\";\n",[64,367,368],{"class":66,"line":94},[64,369,370],{},"import ReactDOM from 'react-dom\u002Fclient'\n",[64,372,373],{"class":66,"line":100},[64,374,375],{},"import App from '.\u002FApp'\n",[64,377,378],{"class":66,"line":106},[64,379,380],{},"import ToDoList from '.\u002FToDoList'\n",[64,382,383],{"class":66,"line":112},[64,384,385],{},"import Products from '.\u002FProducts'\n",[64,387,388],{"class":66,"line":118},[64,389,390],{},"import Admin from '.\u002FAdmin'\n",[64,392,393],{"class":66,"line":124},[64,394,395],{},"import '.\u002Findex.css';\n",[64,397,398],{"class":66,"line":245},[64,399,401],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":400},true,"\n",[64,403,404],{"class":66,"line":251},[64,405,406],{},"ReactDOM.createRoot(document.getElementById('root')).render(\n",[64,408,409],{"class":66,"line":257},[64,410,411],{},"  \u003CReact.StrictMode>\n",[64,413,415],{"class":66,"line":414},12,[64,416,417],{},"    \u003CHashRouter>\n",[64,419,421],{"class":66,"line":420},13,[64,422,423],{},"      \u003Cnav className=\"px-5 flex items-center h-[60px] bg-indigo-500 text-white\">\n",[64,425,427],{"class":66,"line":426},14,[64,428,429],{},"        \u003Ch1 className=\"mr-auto text-2xl\">React TodoList\u003C\u002Fh1>\n",[64,431,433],{"class":66,"line":432},15,[64,434,435],{},"        \u003Cul className=\"flex\">\n",[64,437,439],{"class":66,"line":438},16,[64,440,441],{},"          \u003Cli className=\"mr-3\">\n",[64,443,445],{"class":66,"line":444},17,[64,446,447],{},"            \u003CNavLink to=\"\u002Fhome\" className=\"border p-3 hover:bg-indigo-600 duration-500\"\n",[64,449,451],{"class":66,"line":450},18,[64,452,453],{},"            >Home\u003C\u002FNavLink>\n",[64,455,457],{"class":66,"line":456},19,[64,458,459],{},"          \u003C\u002Fli>\n",[64,461,463],{"class":66,"line":462},20,[64,464,441],{},[64,466,468],{"class":66,"line":467},21,[64,469,470],{},"            \u003CNavLink to=\"\u002Ftodolist\" className=\"border p-3 hover:bg-indigo-600 duration-500\">ToDoList\u003C\u002FNavLink>\n",[64,472,474],{"class":66,"line":473},22,[64,475,459],{},[64,477,479],{"class":66,"line":478},23,[64,480,441],{},[64,482,484],{"class":66,"line":483},24,[64,485,486],{},"          \u003CNavLink to='\u002Fproducts'\n",[64,488,490],{"class":66,"line":489},25,[64,491,492],{},"            className=\"border p-3 hover:bg-indigo-600 duration-500\"\n",[64,494,496],{"class":66,"line":495},26,[64,497,498],{},"            >Product Detail\u003C\u002FNavLink>\n",[64,500,502],{"class":66,"line":501},27,[64,503,459],{},[64,505,507],{"class":66,"line":506},28,[64,508,441],{},[64,510,512],{"class":66,"line":511},29,[64,513,514],{},"          \u003CNavLink to='\u002Fadmin'\n",[64,516,518],{"class":66,"line":517},30,[64,519,492],{},[64,521,523],{"class":66,"line":522},31,[64,524,525],{},"            >Admin\u003C\u002FNavLink>\n",[64,527,529],{"class":66,"line":528},32,[64,530,459],{},[64,532,534],{"class":66,"line":533},33,[64,535,536],{},"        \u003C\u002Ful>\n",[64,538,540],{"class":66,"line":539},34,[64,541,542],{},"      \u003C\u002Fnav>\n",[64,544,546],{"class":66,"line":545},35,[64,547,548],{},"      \u003CRoutes>\n",[64,550,552],{"class":66,"line":551},36,[64,553,554],{},"        \u003CRoute path=\"\u002F\" element={ \u003CApp \u002F> } \u002F>\n",[64,556,558],{"class":66,"line":557},37,[64,559,560],{},"        \u003CRoute path=\"\u002Ftodolist\" element={ \u003CToDoList \u002F> } \u002F>\n",[64,562,564],{"class":66,"line":563},38,[64,565,566],{},"        \u003CRoute path=\"\u002Fproducts\" element={ \u003CProducts \u002F> } \u002F>\n",[64,568,570],{"class":66,"line":569},39,[64,571,572],{},"        \u003CRoute path=\"\u002Fadmin\" element={ \u003CAdmin \u002F> } \u002F>\n",[64,574,576],{"class":66,"line":575},40,[64,577,578],{},"      \u003C\u002FRoutes>\n",[64,580,582],{"class":66,"line":581},41,[64,583,584],{},"    \u003C\u002FHashRouter>\n",[64,586,588],{"class":66,"line":587},42,[64,589,590],{},"  \u003C\u002FReact.StrictMode>\n",[64,592,594],{"class":66,"line":593},43,[64,595,596],{},")\n",[17,598,599,600,602,603,606,607,609],{},"Now open your browser, inspect the page, and find the ",[21,601,307],{}," link for the current page. You'll notice the class has an extra ",[21,604,605],{},"active"," on it — and that ",[21,608,605],{}," means you're currently on this page:",[17,611,612],{},[613,614],"img",{"alt":615,"src":616},"the active class on the current nav link","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FJavaScript\u002F%E4%BE%86%E8%87%AA%20Vue%20%E7%9A%84%20React%20Hook%20%E9%96%8B%E7%99%BC%E8%80%85\u002F%E8%B2%BC%E4%B8%8A%E7%9A%84%E5%BD%B1%E5%83%8F_2022_7_16_21_44.png",[17,618,619,620,622],{},"And when you switch pages, this ",[21,621,605],{}," class automatically moves over too:",[17,624,625],{},[613,626],{"alt":627,"src":628},"active class switching as you navigate","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FJavaScript\u002F%E4%BE%86%E8%87%AA%20Vue%20%E7%9A%84%20React%20Hook%20%E9%96%8B%E7%99%BC%E8%80%85\u002FJul-16-2022%2021-46-26.gif",[17,630,631],{},"So with this, we can hugely improve the user experience — letting people know exactly which page they're on just from the navbar.",[17,633,634,635,637,638,641],{},"If you want to customize the ",[21,636,605],{}," class name — say, change it to ",[21,639,640],{},"router-link-active"," — you can do it like this:",[55,643,645],{"className":57,"code":644,"language":59,"meta":60,"style":60},"\u003CNavLink\n  to=\"\u002F\"\n  className={({ isActive }) => isActive ? 'router-link-active' : null }\n  >\n  Home\n\u003C\u002FNavLink>\n",[21,646,647,652,657,662,667,672],{"__ignoreMap":60},[64,648,649],{"class":66,"line":67},[64,650,651],{},"\u003CNavLink\n",[64,653,654],{"class":66,"line":88},[64,655,656],{},"  to=\"\u002F\"\n",[64,658,659],{"class":66,"line":94},[64,660,661],{},"  className={({ isActive }) => isActive ? 'router-link-active' : null }\n",[64,663,664],{"class":66,"line":100},[64,665,666],{},"  >\n",[64,668,669],{"class":66,"line":106},[64,670,671],{},"  Home\n",[64,673,674],{"class":66,"line":112},[64,675,676],{},"\u003C\u002FNavLink>\n",[17,678,679,680,682,683,686],{},"But now we run into a problem: the ",[21,681,30],{}," we wrote already has a ",[21,684,685],{},"className"," on it:",[55,688,690],{"className":57,"code":689,"language":59,"meta":60,"style":60},"\u003CNavLink\n  to=\"\u002F\"\n  className=\"border p-3 hover:bg-indigo-600 duration-500\"\n>\n  Home\n\u003C\u002FNavLink>\n",[21,691,692,696,700,705,710,714],{"__ignoreMap":60},[64,693,694],{"class":66,"line":67},[64,695,651],{},[64,697,698],{"class":66,"line":88},[64,699,656],{},[64,701,702],{"class":66,"line":94},[64,703,704],{},"  className=\"border p-3 hover:bg-indigo-600 duration-500\"\n",[64,706,707],{"class":66,"line":100},[64,708,709],{},">\n",[64,711,712],{"class":66,"line":106},[64,713,671],{},[64,715,716],{"class":66,"line":112},[64,717,676],{},[17,719,720,721,724,725,31],{},"If you tack on another ",[21,722,723],{},"className={({ isActive }) => isActive ? 'router-link-active' : null }",", you'll get this error: ",[21,726,727],{},"warning: Duplicate key \"className\" in object literal",[17,729,730],{},"So how do we fix it? If you want both at the same time, you have to change it to this:",[55,732,734],{"className":57,"code":733,"language":59,"meta":60,"style":60},"\u003CNavLink\n  to=\"\u002F\"\n  className={({ isActive }) => \n    [\n      'border p-3 hover:bg-indigo-600 duration-500',\n      isActive ? 'router-link-active' : null\n    ].join(' ')\n  }\n>\n  Home\n\u003C\u002FNavLink>\n",[21,735,736,740,744,749,754,759,764,769,773,777,781],{"__ignoreMap":60},[64,737,738],{"class":66,"line":67},[64,739,651],{},[64,741,742],{"class":66,"line":88},[64,743,656],{},[64,745,746],{"class":66,"line":94},[64,747,748],{},"  className={({ isActive }) => \n",[64,750,751],{"class":66,"line":100},[64,752,753],{},"    [\n",[64,755,756],{"class":66,"line":106},[64,757,758],{},"      'border p-3 hover:bg-indigo-600 duration-500',\n",[64,760,761],{"class":66,"line":112},[64,762,763],{},"      isActive ? 'router-link-active' : null\n",[64,765,766],{"class":66,"line":118},[64,767,768],{},"    ].join(' ')\n",[64,770,771],{"class":66,"line":124},[64,772,121],{},[64,774,775],{"class":66,"line":245},[64,776,709],{},[64,778,779],{"class":66,"line":251},[64,780,671],{},[64,782,783],{"class":66,"line":257},[64,784,676],{},[17,786,787,788,790,791,793],{},"That way you can keep your styles and the ",[21,789,605],{},"-state styling at the same time. And here's the styling for when ",[21,792,640],{}," kicks in — add this to your index.css:",[55,795,799],{"className":796,"code":797,"language":798,"meta":60,"style":60},"language-css shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast",".router-link-active {\n  @apply bg-indigo-800;\n}\n","css",[21,800,801,811,825],{"__ignoreMap":60},[64,802,803,807],{"class":66,"line":67},[64,804,806],{"class":805},"sCcAr",".router-link-active",[64,808,810],{"class":809},"sMAXC"," {\n",[64,812,813,816,819,822],{"class":66,"line":88},[64,814,815],{"class":809},"  @",[64,817,818],{"class":805},"apply",[64,820,821],{"class":805}," bg-indigo-",[64,823,824],{"class":809},"800;\n",[64,826,827],{"class":66,"line":94},[64,828,829],{"class":809},"}\n",[17,831,832,833,835],{},"With this approach you get nav tracking that applies the ",[21,834,640],{}," style:",[17,837,838],{},[613,839],{"alt":840,"src":841},"router-link-active style applied to the current nav link","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FJavaScript\u002F%E4%BE%86%E8%87%AA%20Vue%20%E7%9A%84%20React%20Hook%20%E9%96%8B%E7%99%BC%E8%80%85\u002FJul-16-2022%2022-41-57.gif",[17,843,844,845,847,848,851,852,854,855,857],{},"One extra heads-up: you might come across people saying ",[21,846,30],{}," can use ",[21,849,850],{},"activeClassName"," to change the ",[21,853,605],{}," class name. But ",[21,856,850],{}," was actually deprecated after React Router 6, so if you try to use it you'll hit this error:",[859,860,861],"blockquote",{},[17,862,863,864,866,867,870],{},"Warning: React does not recognize the ",[21,865,850],{}," prop on a DOM element. If you intentionally want it to appear in the DOM as a custom attribute, spell it as lowercase ",[21,868,869],{},"activeclassname"," instead. If you accidentally passed it from a parent component, remove it from the DOM element.",[17,872,873,874,878],{},"The example code for this part is ",[307,875,312],{"href":876,"rel":877},"https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fexample-react-router-link\u002Ftree\u002Ffeature\u002Fnavlink",[311]," too.",[12,880,882],{"id":881},"afterword","Afterword",[17,884,885],{},"This post is also published on my blog:",[136,887,888],{},[139,889,890],{},[307,891,894],{"href":892,"rel":893},"https:\u002F\u002Fisraynotarray.com\u002F",[311],"Is Ray Not Array",[896,897,898],"style",{},"html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html pre.shiki code .sCcAr, html code.shiki .sCcAr{--shiki-default:#91CBFF}html pre.shiki code .sMAXC, html code.shiki .sMAXC{--shiki-default:#F0F3F6}",{"title":60,"searchDepth":88,"depth":88,"links":900},[901,902,903,904],{"id":14,"depth":88,"text":15},{"id":34,"depth":88,"text":23},{"id":315,"depth":88,"text":30},{"id":881,"depth":88,"text":882},"React","2022-10-10 00:00:01","We touched on Link earlier, but we never really got to know it properly — we just showed how to use it and moved on. So this post takes a closer look at Link, and along the way introduces another piece: NavLink. We'll walk through Link's props (including the tricky state one in React Router v6), then build a navbar with NavLink so it can track the current page and style itself accordingly.","md","en",{},"\u002Fen\u002Freact\u002Flearn-react-now-26-react-router-link-navlink","4",{"title":6,"description":907},false,"en\u002FReact\u002Flearn-react-now-26-react-router-link-navlink",[917,918,919,920,921],"You'll Learn React Eventually, So Why Not Now?","React Basics","React Router","React Router Link","React Router NavLink",null,"\u002Fen\u002Freact\u002F2022\u002F10\u002F10\u002Flearn-react-now-26-react-router-link-navlink\u002F","JtnMyRKd1qDEwnsCwBAccH6YHKVEoLn80WlcOGTGZQc",{"newer":926,"older":930},{"url":927,"title":928,"date":929},"\u002Fen\u002Freact\u002F2022\u002F10\u002F11\u002Freact-day-27-react-router-hooks\u002F","React, Why Not Learn It Now? - The React Router Hooks You'll Actually Use - (27)","2022-10-11 00:00:01",{"url":931,"title":932,"date":933},"\u002Fen\u002Freact\u002F2022\u002F10\u002F09\u002Freact-day-25-react-router-nested-routes\u002F","React, Why Not Learn It Now? - React Router - Nested Routes - (25)","2022-10-09 00:00:01",[935,939,944],{"url":936,"title":937,"date":938,"readingMinutes":912},"\u002Fen\u002Freact\u002F2022\u002F10\u002F14\u002Flearn-react-now-30-wrap-up-and-toc\u002F","Learn React Now — Wrap-up Notes & Full Table of Contents (30)","2022-10-14 00:00:01",{"url":940,"title":941,"date":942,"readingMinutes":943},"\u002Fen\u002Freact\u002F2022\u002F10\u002F13\u002Flearn-react-29-react-redux-quick-start\u002F","Learn React Eventually, So Why Not Now? - React Redux: Redux and a Quick Start - (29)","2022-10-13 00:00:01","6",{"url":945,"title":946,"date":947,"readingMinutes":912},"\u002Fen\u002Freact\u002F2022\u002F10\u002F12\u002Freact-day-28-router-lazy-loading\u002F","Why Learn React Eventually? Learn It Now! - React Router Lazy Loading (28)","2022-10-12 00:00:01",1784013072987]